I would've rated five stars, if it wasn't for the fact that this game has NO slow-down, or rewind button. Devs, why would you give the players a pause, play, and fast-forward button, but NOT any of the other buttons? To take into consideration: players could use a rewind button to prevent a mistake, without having to restart an entire level over again. Also, a slow-down button would DRASTICALLY help players time stuff like kamikaze explosions, and zombie transformations ALMOST perfectly!

Love this game from start to finish. Everything about it screams class. The graphics are brilliantly done and the sound effects and Pingu like speech is just spot on. Don't be fooled though, it is a tricky game making you trial and error to find the best solution. That said the learning curve is generous. Great range of zombie types and levels to clear. Best described as Lemmings meets 28 days later, it is a joy to control the tiny pixellated undead as they try to enslave the world. A must buy.

First off, I wanted to commend you on making a true paid game from what I see. No microtransactions at all, I no longer play f2p games because the amount of corruption. Then the art you did it in a way to makes it feel like it's not like the other copy paste art styles of other moble games. Worth the $8 no regrets! Underrated in my book! 5/5*

Needed to drop another star.  The more I play the more of an issue it is. Some UI scaling should be in place. I play on a large phone (s10 +) and not even the main menu is all that usable, let alone reading the story text. Please resolve this. You're ruining one of the best real time puzzles games I played (on other devices)
replyContent: Hey Chris, you are right that the UI is not very well suited for small devices, our original plan was to target only tablets above 7 inches but we choose to not apply this limit because not everyone will bother by that. We had to compromise to reflect that. We cannot make it too big either or it would cover too much screen space...

replyContent: Hey, the dialogues as been fixed for quite some times now (in version 1.0.1 if recall correctly), the files got corrupted somehow. Sorry about the delay to reply to your review, we appreciate the feedback.
